messages: 268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:43): Well enough of the pity party
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:43): Kill them with fire. Hilarious fire.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:44): how many clowns can you get into a bone fire?
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:44): Give or take a few red noses
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:45): I wonder if the red noses melt to the skin inside the fire
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:46): Cooking with clowns. Shame I'm vegetarian
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:46): I hear the painted faces are bad for you anyway
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:47): Yeah, something to do with lead, or summat. Prob taste like chicken anyway
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:47): I hear it tastes like alligator
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:47): I hear alligator tastes like chicken
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:48): I've eaten alligator! And ostrich. Yep, chicken - all of it.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:49): The computers couldn't generate anymore tastes, so they made everything taste like chicken
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:49): Poor chickens. They get no love.
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:50): I learned it from my learnings
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:50): I just thought they glided with grace
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:51): I have seen many a things as i taveled through this wayward land, but never have I seen a chiken fly
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:52): IIt's true! Farmers clip their wings so they're grounded and whatnot. Honest!
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:52): Also, there once was a chicken that lived for 2 years....without a HEAD! Trufax.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:53): hints the saying,"Running around like a chicken with its head cut off."
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:53): Indeed! He choked to death in the end. V sad. I cry every day.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:54): We should do somthing about the choking chicken problem
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:54): I think so. A National Don't Choke a Chicken Day. Oo-er.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:55): We have to get more women involved for it to ever work
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:56): It's a dirty job, but someone's gotta do it.
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:57): Cool convo, bro. Gotta say, your the first person who doesn't spout a/s/l every 2 secs.
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:58): Where u at anyway? Other than not-Australia.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (17:59): Well, you know it is humanly impossiple to carry on a conversation with someone without knowing their age and loaction
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (17:59): Hee! The UK. The cold and raing bit (Wales).
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:00): Cool and Rainy here, Birmingham, AL
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:00): I've been to Birmingham! The one in England. Also rainy. Who'd've thunk it?
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:01): Guess not! Think your B'ham is bigger though!
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:02): Sorry, The Office joke. Though it is the US version!
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:03): It's what we do over here to pass the time
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:03): Lucky you. All we do is farm sheep and dragons.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:04): i have always wanted a pet dragon, but I am allergic to fire
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:05): Aw. I could de-flame one for you? Not so good for burning clowns, though.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:05): Did not know of this de-flaming procedure
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:05): I sleep on a Serta, so i got plenty of sheep
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:06): Just feed it a few newborn humans and it's good for life. No more scorch marcks on the curtains.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:07): The clowns would never see it coming
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:07): Bwa ha ha! Take THAT Bonzo!
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:08): I shall name my sheep Mutton-Belly.
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:08): Especially effective on New Zealand clowns.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:08): I think I am going with Cotton Ball.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:09): I think you need to sheep attached at the hip for that name to be appropiate
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:09): Nice image! Deceptively cute. I like it.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:10): i bet you could saddle it too
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:10): D'aw! Two for the price of one. Hi-ho fluffy away.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:11): Then you can shoot fire it differnet directions
93805442bbfdf9f6d90b17683e52e5c1 (18:12): That's it, I'm customising the flock. Pimp My Ewe.
268c881eb565999ac2f79247e9fd407a (18:12): Dualing sheep, the greatest weapon ever?
